climbs.name: Summer School
climbs.fa: Alan Bartlett and Eric Anderson, July 1990

content.description: This is a rather low quality route, with jams and liebacks.  It is not sustained.
content.location: This climb starts at the same place as Orgasmatron, but stays right in thin cracks

climbs.name: Phil E. Pino
climbs.fa: Todd Swain, Peggy Buckey and Jeff Rickerl May 1992

content.description: This is the short, contrived two bolt route just left of Marcos.  Great rock and excellent climbing.  Better to start out on Marcos and move left over to the first bolt.
content.protection: A couple of finger to hand sized pieces for the start of Marcos, two good bolts and a small TCU for the last move.  2-3" cams for the belay.
content.location: This route is on the face 5 feet left of Marcos.  It is further right than shown on Randy's excellent JT West guidebook.  Hike down to the left (east).

climbs.name: Orgasmatron, The
climbs.fa: Eric Anderson, Todd Gordon, Todd Swain, and Alan Bartlett, June 1990

content.description: This is a crack route with a hand jamming crux.

climbs.name: Marcos
climbs.fa: Dave Evans and Todd Gordon, Feb. 1986

content.description: This is a clean hand and finger crack in a dihedral.  Since this route is short and starts half way up the wall, it can be combined with Exiled in one pitch.

climbs.name: Imelda's New Shoes
climbs.fa: Todd Gordon, Todd Swain, Eric Anderson, and Alan Bartlett, June, 1990

content.description: This is a fun, varied climb, with a crux thin crack near the start, and flared hand jams, steep face, and liebacks above.
content.location: This route is at the left end of the wall.

climbs.name: Granulator, The
climbs.fa: Eric Anderson and Alan Bartlett, July 1990

content.description: This is a high quality, varied climb, with many interesting crack and face moves.

climbs.name: Exiled
climbs.fa: Richard Shoup, Bart Groendycke, and Todd Alston

content.description: steep face climbing up a thin crack system
content.location: This is a short route at the right end of the wall.

content.description: Crux comes after entering the squeeze section of the chimney.  It's a little grainy in the chimney but fun if you like squeezes.
content.location:
Same start of

Aquino

but step right at base of flake to enter chimney.

climbs.name: Aquino
climbs.fa: Todd Gordon and Dave Evans, Feb. 1986

content.description: This is a crack climb, with a nice stemming entry move and hand jams above, but with several large, loose holds.
